Preconditions:
The input array "fruits" must not be null.
The input array "fruits" must have at least one row.
The input array "fruits" must have at least one column.
The value of "startPos" must be a valid index within the range of the input array "fruits".
The value of "k" must be a positive integer.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the maximum total number of fruits that can be harvested.
The input array "fruits" should remain unchanged after the method is executed.
The values of "startPos" and "k" should remain unchanged after the method is executed.